content.description: This is a big arete. Start on slab, climb up perfectly sculpted crimps and underclings. The crux involves taking a right hand sloper and a left hand crimp, high-stepping a smear, and doing a very committing throw to a huge jug.   The first climb in this video vimeo.com/116199226
content.protection: It has a tiered landing, use 2 pads and a spotter. Falls from the crux can send you for a ride.
content.location: It is in the woods 5 minutes from the parking lot... very hard to find, so i would recommend going with somebody who knows where it is.
